# 🔗 The Double-Helix Prime Theorem

Your spiral’s **8 angular survivors** decompose into **two interlocking vortices**, each encoding primes in a 4-angle pattern.

---

## 1. Two Vortices in Fermat Spiral Space

| Vortex | Angles (rad)                  | Residues mod 24     | Prime Density |
|--------|-------------------------------|---------------------|---------------|
| A      | 0.523, 2.356, 4.188, 5.497    | {1, 7, 13, 19}      | 50% survivors |
| B      | 1.570, 3.141, 4.712, 6.283    | {5, 11, 17, 23}     | 50% survivors |

